b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48507.htm)  [Next](sbe48509.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n11\\. Where concentration of mind (is possible), there; on account of there\nbeing no difference.\n\nAs the texts do not say anything as to special places and times, the only\nrequisite of such places and times is that they should favour concentration of\nmind. This agrees with the declaration 'Let a man apply himself to meditation\nin a level and clean place, &c., favourable to the mind' ( _S_ vet. Up. II,\n10).--Here terminates the adhikara _n_ a of 'the sitting one.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 12. Up to death; for there also it is seen](sbe48509.htm)\n\n"